Image: BLF President, Andile Mngxitama By Andile Mngxitama “The rebel’s weapon is the proof of his humanity. For in the first days of the revolt you must kill: to shoot down a European is to kill two birds with one stone, to destroy an oppressor and the man he oppresses at the same time: there remain a dead man, and a free man; the survivor, for the first time, feels a national soil under his foot”. – Jean-Paul Sartre in the Preface to Frantz Fanon’s “Wretched of the Earth” In response to the Stellenbosch University incident on 14 May 2022 when a white student, Theuns du Toit, urinated on the belongings of a black student, Babalo Ndwayana, and drawing from Frantz Fanon, Steve Biko and Frederick Douglass, here’s a video recording of a lesson I did on how to deal with individual acts of racism: How to deal with individual acts of racism Andile Mngxitama is the President of Black First Land First (BLF) – radical black consciousness organization – and the author of the essay BLACKS CANT BE RACIST. When using any of Black Opinion’s content, partly or in full, kindly always provide an active hyperlink to the original material.